======Empyre======
The Shi'ar monitored [[Theodore Altman (Earth-616)|Hulkling]] as he ascended to the throne of the [[Kree/Skrull Alliance (Earth-616)|Kree-Skrull Alliance]].<!-- {{r|King in Black: Wiccan and Hulkling #1}} -->

After the resolution of the [[Empyre (Event)|conflicts]] sparked by the merger of the Kree and Skrull, vice-chancellor [[T'Kao (Earth-616)|T'Kao]], the representative of the [[Shi'ar Empire]] to Emperor Hulkling offered and his husband [[William Kaplan (Earth-616)|Wiccan]] a honeymoon on [[Little Chandilar]] as wedding gift.{{r|King in Black: Wiccan and Hulkling #1}}

Meanwhile, a diplomatic summit was convened at the [[Proscenium]] to explore how intergalactic relations would be impacted by the new alliance, to discuss the status of the [[Pan-Worlds Treaties]], and to seek a path towards stability and peace among the assembled factions. In attendance were representatives of the Kree/Skrull Alliance, the [[Utopian Kree]] faction, the [[Kymellians]], the [[Rigellians]], [[Earth]], the [[Galactic Rim Collective]], the [[Badoon Sisterhood (Earth-616)|Badoon]] (in fact the weapons dealer and [[Elders of the Universe (Earth-616)|Elder of the Universe]] known as the [[Profiteer (Earth-616)|Profiteer]]), [[Spartax (Planet)|Spartax]], the [[Chitauri]], the [[Zn'rx Empire|Zn'rx]], and the Shi'ar, represented by [[Subguardian Oracle-2 (Earth-616)|Oracle-2]].<!-- {{r|Guardians of the Galaxy Vol 6 7|8}} -->

Chaos ensued when the Profiteer, hoping to precipitate another Snarkwar (and the resulting lucrative weapons market), assassinated the Emperor. Further efforts to destabilize the conference were exposed when the attending Chitauri representative, the diplomat-drone [[Peacebringer (Earth-616)|Peacebringer]], was revealed to have been created as a walking bio-explosive bomb.{{r|Guardians of the Galaxy Vol 6 7|8}}

======The King in Black======
While Hulkling and Wiccan (along with [[Lauri-Ell (Earth-616)|Lauri-Ell, the Accuser]]) were on Little Chandilar, the planet was attacked by the forces of the [[Glossary:Elder Gods|ancient entity]] [[knull (Earth-616)|Knull]]: [[Symbiote Dragons]], and the Kree of [[Talos (Earth-616)|Talos]] (lost to the Symbiotes [[Web of Venom: Empyre's End Vol 1 1|earlier]]). Hulkling, Wiccan and Lauri-Ell fought the Symbiotes and led the evacuation of the planet.{{r|King in Black: Wiccan and Hulkling #1}}

In the midst of the Proscenium summit chaos,<!-- the information was passed to the conference's members as the two hostiles had been unveiled (though not subdued) --> those in attendance received word that planets within Shi'ar Space (along with many other worlds) were being stripped of life by the advance of Knull.{{r|Guardians of the Galaxy Vol 6 8}}

Afterwards, several Shi'ar colonies fell to the [[Symbiote Dragons]] (at least four during a single week).{{r|S.W.O.R.D. Vol 2 4}}

